\i\f1\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid15221682 
This research discusses about analysis of the implementation of Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) of PT PLN Indonesia Power UP Indralaya in improving the community economy in Payakabung Village. The aim of this research is to describe the implementati
on of Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) of PT PLN Indonesia Power UP Indralaya in improving the economy of the community in Payakabung Village and knowing the impact of implementing CSR. The research method used in this research is qualitative researc
h 
with the type of field research. The data collection techniques in this research are: (1) Observation, which aims to observe conditions in the field related to the implementation of CSR in improving the community's economy, (2) Interview, which aims to ob
tain in-depth information from several related informants, (3) Documentation Study, which the aim is to obtain data through existing documents in the form of archives related to CSR implementation related to company profile, history, vision and mission, o
rg
anizational structure, CSR implementation reports related to research problems. Analysis of the data used through analysis activities before and after in the field. Data analysis before going to the field was carried out by studying literature reviews and
 secondary data. Data analysis in the field is carried out by data reduction, descriptive data presentation, verification and drawing conclusions.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s40\qj \li0\ri0\sa160\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs22\lang1057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f1\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid15221682 The research results show that the implementation of PT PLN Indonesia Power UP Indralaya's CSR has taken place
 from planning activities to the monitoring and evaluation stages of the CSR program. The research results also show that the implementation of CSR has had a positive impact on society which has led to economic improvements such as increasing people's inc
ome, providing employment opportunities, environmental management activities, and increasing people's knowledge and skills.
